      "writtenOn": "2026-05-07T17:31:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My original thinking was that the responder firmware decides the reset semantics, so the BMC just reports what the device does. The Redfish flow is also: caller POSTs ResetType, and if not specified, falls back to this property\u0027s value as the default.\n\nBut you have a valid point — readonly single value forces a one-reset-type-per-device assumption, which doesn\u0027t match Redfish\u0027s AllowableValues (an array). Would it work better if I:\n - Change the property to SupportedResetTypes as array[enum] (readonly, reported by firmware)\n - The first entry is treated as the default when the caller does not specify a type.\n  \nThis way the device can advertise multiple types, and the caller picks one explicitly. WDYT?\nThanks!",
      "parentUuid": "9ba30815_5a31d5c2",
      "revId": "379ab5afb8ba0de7286dd93cc5afb5c0e22ea3bd",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
